## PART IV — FINDING 3: DEPTH + CT ANTIGEN + TREG RATIO
## CO-VARY AT THE DEEP END (The Mechanistic Chain)

### Framework finding (S3-P8 + S3-P9 + S3-P10 combined):
The memory-low group (deepest TYPE 4) simultaneously has:
  — Higher depth scores (p=5.52e-08, ratio=3.17×)
  — Higher CT antigen de-repression (p=8.86e-09)
  — Higher FOXP3/CD8A ratio (p=0.008)

The framework's mechanistic interpretation:
  Deep root lock → bilateral identity absence
  → CT antigen de-repression
  → Immune system recognises CT antigens
  → Immune cells recruited
  → Tregs expand to suppress recognition
  → Net OS null in untreated patients (S3-P7)
  → Greatest predicted benefit from anti-TIGIT + anti-PD-1

### Literature:

**On the co-variation of CT antigen expression and Treg infiltration:**

No published paper has directly reported a co-variation
between CT antigen level and Treg/effector ratio within
claudin-low breast cancer or any comparable cancer subtype.
The conceptual link (CT antigen → immune attraction →
Treg suppression) is logically derivable from first
principles but has not been tested or stated in this form.

**The immune cancellation concept (CT antigen + Treg = OS null):**

The general principle that two opposing immune forces can
cancel in untreated patients is well-established:

— Multiple papers on TIL prognosis in breast cancer note that
the prognostic significance of immune infiltrates depends
on composition (cytotoxic vs regulatory), not total
infiltrate level. High total TIL with high FOXP3 does
not confer the same benefit as high total TIL with high
CD8. The ratio is the key variable, not the magnitude
(BJS 2016, BMC Cancer 2021).

— The concept that CT antigen recognition is suppressed by
Tregs in untreated tumours (leaving OS null) and would be
unmasked by Treg depletion is implicitly supported by the
Morel JCI 2017 finding (anti-PD-1 worsens claudin-low
outcomes by amplifying Tregs) and the Frontiers Immunology
2020 CAR-T paper (which notes that Treg depletion is
required before CT antigen-targeting CAR-T can be
effective in solid tumours).

**Status: NOVEL ✦ — as a unified mechanistic chain**

The individual components are in the literature. The
specific chain (root lock depth → CT antigen de-repression
→ Treg-suppressed immune cancellation → OS null untreated
→ greatest anti-TIGIT benefit) has not been published as
a unified mechanism. The co-variation of all three
properties within a single cancer type's depth axis
has not been published. This is an original framework
synthesis finding.

